[emph]public function getNotification()[/emph]

The Phprojekt_Item_Abstract have this function that return a Phprojekt_Notification class,
where are defined all the function for make and send a notification mail about the item.
If your module have special ways for do that, like set special recipients, or an special body of the email,
you must:
In the model, define the function like:

[code]
public function getNotification()
{
    $notification = Phprojekt_Loader::getModel('MyModule', 'Notification');
    $notification->setModel($this);

    return $notification;
}
[/code]

and make a class into applications/MyModule/Models named Notification.php
where you will define the necessaries functions.
Since this function should be an extension of Phprojekt_Notification,
you need to re-write only the functions that work different.
See the Phprojekt_Notification documentation for know more about this class.
